    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p>Married by the&#8212;<persName role="author">Isaac M. Slatky</persName><lb/> on the <date><sic>18. Menachim <hi rend="underline">5&#59;612</hi></sic> &#40;Augt. 3D <hi rend="underline">1852</hi></date><lb/> <persName>Mr Isaac Michael</persName> to <persName>Mrs<lb/> Hannah Tobias</persName> Both of the City <placeName><sic>St Luis</sic><lb/> Miss</placeName><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Isaac. M. Slatky</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>No 134 Elliott St.  Buffalo N. Y.</placeName></p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>Revd.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Editor of the Occident</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><hi rend="underline">paid</hi></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Buffalo</placeName>&#44; <date>Tuesday evening&#44; 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Ab&#44; 5612</date></p>
			<p>To my trusted friend&#44; the very learned and accomplished<lb/> <addressee>Rabbi Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; long may he live&#44; Amen.</p>
			<p>My beloved&#44; my friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">At this time I shall not write at length&#44; for I am heavy<lb/> of speech and of tongue&#44; and am not able to speak the Hebrew language<lb/> in its purity.  But&#44; I come to let you know that I have received a<lb/> brief letter from your High Honor&#44; by the hand of <persName>Mr. Bernheimer.</persName><lb/>  He told me that I really have no need of this trouble of going from<lb/> house to house&#44; and this way and that&#44; to seek for subscribers to<lb/> the Bible which is to be translated into English by your worthy self.<lb/>  I&#44; therefore&#44; write this letter to Your Worthiness to let you know<lb/> that I&#44; the least in the tribes of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; am ready to<lb/> take from Your Honor one set&#44; the price of which I shall send after<lb/> the <date>Rosh ha&#45;shana</date> that is approaching.  I also desire a prayer book<lb/> for holidays of the Polish ritual&#44; if you have one.  If so&#44; please<lb/> let me know before the <date>Rosh Hodesh of Ellul</date> coming.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In passing I cannot refrain to give you a small bit<lb/> of news to be included in the Occident of the coming month&#59;&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">&#8220;Married by the &#95;&#95;<persName role="author">Isaac M. Slatky</persName> on the <date>18 Menahim&#42; 5&#59;612<lb/> &#40; August 3d 1852&#41;</date> <persName>Mr. Isaac Michael</persName> to <persName>Mrs. Hannah Tobias</persName>&#44; both<lb/> of the City of <placeName>St. Louis Miss.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have no further news.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">He who seeks his peoples welfare&#44; and who hopes for<lb/> your answer&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Isaac Slatkin</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Address &#8212; <placeName>134 Ellicott St.&#44; Buffalo N. Y.</placeName></p>
			<p>I hope that Your High Honor will send me a letter without any delay.</p>
			<p>flowery Hebrew&#8212;tis none too pure</p>
			<p>&#42; <date>Ab</date></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
